---
import TrustPageLayout from "~/layouts/TrustPageLayout.astro";
---

<TrustPageLayout
  title="Submit a tip — DubaiPoints"
  description="Spotted a UAE bank changing salary-transfer terms, an airline running an unannounced bonus, or a card review that reads like marketing? Tell us."
  eyebrow="Tip line"
  heading="Tell us what we missed."
  deck="If a UAE bank's terms changed quietly, an airline ran an unannounced bonus, or a card on this site has a fee we got wrong — let us know. We treat every tip as confidential by default."
  lastUpdated={new Date("2026-05-09")}
>
  <section>
    <h2>What's worth tipping</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Salary-transfer offers (cash, vouchers, combined card+salary promotions) — especially before the bank's site updates.</li>
      <li>Card terms changing (annual fee, FX fee, minimum salary, welcome bonus mechanics).</li>
      <li>Airline / hotel bonuses we haven't covered.</li>
      <li>Customer service patterns from a UAE bank — recurring rejections at a specific salary band, salary-transfer reversals, application timelines.</li>
      <li>Anything that reads like marketing on this site and shouldn't.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to send</h2>
    <p>Email <a href="mailto:info@dubaipoints.ae?subject=Tip">info@dubaipoints.ae</a> with what you saw, when you saw it, and — if you have one — a screenshot or document. The subject line "<em>Tip</em>" routes it directly.</p>
    <p>If your tip is sensitive (e.g. you're a bank employee with information about an unpublished change), say so in the email. We do not publish names, employers or any identifying detail without explicit permission.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What we'll do</h2>
    <p>Acknowledge within one business day. Verify against the bank's official channel (product page, schedule of charges, or relationship-manager confirmation) before publishing. If we publish, the source remains confidential by default. If we can't verify, we tell you.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What we won't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Pay for tips. This is a journalism site, not a brokerage.</li>
      <li>Publish unverified claims. A tip is the start of reporting, not the end.</li>
      <li>Reveal a source. Confidential is confidential.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="related">
    <h3>Related</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial policy</a></li>
      <li><a href="/corrections/">Corrections log</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about/">About DubaiPoints</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</TrustPageLayout>
